I think most of these reviews are fake. I’m going to keep it real. I would not recommend this place for individual slices. The food wasn’t that good especially compared to the equally priced but much better food in the area. Blaze Pizza and Pizzeria Regina on Boylston are a two minute walk away and are much better. On a positive note the workers were friendly  and nice. I ordered a cheese slice, buffalo chicken slice and onion rings. The pizza is reminiscent of a Greek style, but poorly done. The cheese slice was slightly soggy, very floppy, had no flavor and there was way too much cheese (not melted and you could still see remnants of the solid chunks of cheese put on the pizza) and barely any sauce. The dough was slightly undercooked. The Buffalo Chicken slice was cooked better, not as soggy and the cheese ratio was better (not good) but the sauce dough and cheese Were bland. The onion rings were crispy but the batter was thick and had very little flavor. Also there were only about 10 onion rings for an order that cost almost $5. I walked in and ordered the slices at 9:30PM on a Monday so I’m not sure if they were sitting around all day. Maybe fresh pizzas are better than the reheated slices. Honestly the 7-11 right around the corner has superior pizza for like $1 a slice.

If you ever want to have a satisfying pizza in the Fenway area look no further than College Pizza. The store owner is a really friendly and helpful guy. He’ll sort you out with your order, gives amazing recommendations and always has a smile on his face. Now that’s what I call excellent customer service. College pizza is my go to outlet whenever I’m hungry and can’t wait for an hour to get a meal. The food tastes wonderful and the service is excellent. The outlet may seem small but don’t go by it’s size. There are a lot of people who swear by College Pizza. They are also open till late night i.e. till about 3-30 or 4-00 AM so you know where to go when you have those late night cravings. They also have Grubhub and other online delivery tie-ups so if you like to skip a visit then you can order online. The cheesy garlic bread and the Pesto pizza are my favorites and on my must-haves list. They also have a really creamy red-velvet cheesecake that satiates your sweet tooth. The pricing is the real deal. If Bang for your buck had a name this would be it.

As someone who lived literally right next to this place and loved it I am shocked by the reviews.  So I am going to break it down as to why I love the place and try to understand the hatred.  The major complaint I see here is the terrible service. One thing you have to inderstand this place is really busy all the time and the guys behind the counter are working really hard to take care of all the orders. Knowing that do not call in for delivery go in and place your order. And while your their say what's up and relax. This place is not for stuck up 20 somethings who expect everything instanteous. It's for people who respect the fact that these guys work really hard and if you respect them back will make sure your food is done in a reasonable amount of time.  Sure you may be thinking if these guys are so over worked then why not change to better system. Well they won't this place runs it old school and makes money doing it. They are not going to change and if you don't like it go to chipotle.  Next up quality of food.  Have some common sense when you walk into the place and ask yourself what do I think this place can make good. Don't go in and order a burger and expect it to be awesome it's a pizza place.  Final thought The buffalo chicken pizza I amazing here and I have not had better anywhere else.

Worst service I've found in the city of Boston. All staff seemed to be stressed as soon as I first entered the place but I found it interesting, the location was practical for me, the prices were good and had an interesting variety of food. When I made my order, I asked how long it would take for my food to be ready, because I planned to wait outside talking to a friend and the guy replied annoyed with the simple question thinking that I wanted to rush him. So when I came back, probably a little before the time he told me, just to check if my food was ready and getting cold on the balcony, the guy started arguing with me in a stupid and idiotic way, just for that because he had me told 10 minutes and I checked earlier. He was stressed out and thought I was in a hurry. I was in no rush. I was just checking, but he was nervous and was aggressively arguing with me "I said to wait 10 minutes, right?". I told him to relax and although he insisted on arguing this nonsense, I withdrew. Then I took my sandwich and it was just ok. Nothing special. I do not plan to go back and I do not recommend this place. To make matters worse, later I talked with some friends and found out that this guy owns the place. What a shame!
